Description:
    Generates a complete impersonation (masquerade) system that allows
    admin users to sign in as other users for debugging and support.

Features:
    - Enhanced MasqueradesController with start/stop actions
    - Impersonation tracking via Session.impersonator association
    - Warning banner displayed when impersonating
    - Security: admins cannot impersonate other admins
    - Optional audit logging integration (if audit_log feature installed)

Example:
    bin/rails generate boilermaker:impersonation

    This will create:
        db/migrate/TIMESTAMP_add_impersonator_to_sessions.rb
        app/controllers/masquerades_controller.rb (enhanced)
        app/components/impersonation_banner.rb
        app/controllers/concerns/impersonation_feature.rb
        config/routes/impersonation.rb
        test/controllers/masquerades_controller_test.rb

Options:
    --skip-routes   Skip generating route file
    --skip-tests    Skip generating test files
    --skip-config   Skip updating boilermaker.yml
    --skip-seeds    Skip adding seed data (n/a for this generator)

Usage:
    1. Start impersonation: POST /users/:user_id/masquerade
    2. Stop impersonation:  DELETE /masquerade
    3. A warning banner appears at the top of the page when impersonating
    4. Click "Exit Impersonation" to return to your admin session

Security:
    - Only users with app_admin=true can impersonate
    - Admins cannot impersonate other admins
    - Impersonation sessions are tracked separately from regular sessions
